<h2 style="font-size:30px;font-family:algerian;text-align:center;background-color:RoyalBlue;">HTML Text Formatting</h2>
<p style="background-color:SteelBlue;">
In this paragraph we will discuss some html formatting elements. 
<br>
<ol>
<b>This is used for bold text. </b> <br>
<strong>This is used for important text. </strong> 
<br>
<i> This is used for italic text. </i> 
<br>
<em>This is used for emphasized text. </em> 
<br>
<mark> This is used for marked text. </mark>
<br>
<small>This is used for small text. </small>
<br>
<del> This is used for deleted text. </del>
<br>
<ins> This is used for inserted text. </ins>
<br>
This is <sub>subscripted </sub> text.
<br>
This is <sup>superscripted </sup> text.
</ol>
<!-- The color property defines the text color for an HTML element -->

<h2 style="font-size:30px;text-align:center;font-family:algerian;background-color:SaddleBrown;">HTML Quotation and Citation Elements</h2>
<!-- <q> element is used for writing quotes -->
<p> WWF goal is to <q>Build a future where people live in harmony and nature.</q></p>
<p>Below article is quoted from Winscp website : </p>
<blockquote cite="https://winscp.net/eng/download.php">
WinSCP 5.13 is a major application update. New features and enhancements include:

Amazon S3 protocol support.
SHA-256 host key fingerprints are used.
Stalled connection attempts can be canceled promptly.
Improvements to .NET assembly and scripting.
List of all changes.
</blockquote>

<!-- abbr element is used for abbreviations -->
<p> The <abbr title="Tata Consultancy Services">TCS</abbr> is world leading company in degrading employees IQ.</p>

<!-- address element is used for contact information of a document or article -->
<address style="background-color:orange;">
House No - 1/399 Housing Board <br>
Kala Kua Alwar <br>
Rajasthan <br>
</address>
<!-- The cite element is used for title of work -->
<p><cite>The Scream</cite> by Edvard Munch. Painted in 1893.</p>
<!-- <bdo> element is used to override the current text direction -->
<bdo dir="rtl">This text will be written from right side to left side.</bdo>
